@node WhatIsIt "Why did you download it if you didn't know what it was?? :-)"
					       @{b}What Is PowerPalette?@{ub}

PowerPalette is basically a palette editor that can jump onto public and private screens, and edit their colours.
It's a commodity, so it can easily be popped up when it's needed.

I can't really think of a specific use to put it to, but this is the sort of program that isn't necessary for
everyday Amiga use, but is essential when a problem pops up which it can sort out. It also has a handy brightness
reduction feature, which reduces the bright colours on a screen so that the screen doesn't flicker on some of the
faulty A1200 batches (mine being one of them).

@endnode

