@Node hiddenpage "Oh no! How did you find this hidden page??"
						   @{b}Hidden Page@{ub}

Man, you must be either a clever old git or a stupid, clumsy gadget presser. Either way, you found your way to the
UNLINKED hidden page!! On this page you will find all sorts of rubbish from deep inside my mind. >>>

How can 69 - 0.3 be equal to be 69? Technically, you must round off your answer to the least number of decimal
places in the numbers; i.e. round off, in this case, to 0 d.p. So, 69 - 0.3 = 68.7, rounding off back up to 69.
This can be very useful to confuse and confound your mates. Or just to annoy them.

0ą = 0, 0˛ = 0. But why, then, does zero to the power of zero equal error (or so it says on my calculator)? Why
not one? Hmm...

Be seeing you...

@EndNode
